---
/**
 * Guided walk — Chapter 5 of 6: "What it costs the public". Narrative prose
 * braided with the Record Teardown teaching component (the Tetra Tech OPC, then
 * the RDA), a transferable-skill takeaway, and exits back into the reference
 * library — the pattern every chapter follows.
 */
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PathWayfinding from "../../components/PathWayfinding.astro";
import RecordTeardown from "../../components/RecordTeardown.astro";
import MoneyFlow from "../../components/islands/MoneyFlow.tsx";
import { OPC_TEARDOWN, RDA_TEARDOWN } from "../../lib/teardowns";
import { buildMoneyFlow, fmtUsd, fmtUsdFull, fmtUsdM } from "../../lib/moneyFlow";
import { chapterByStep, WALK_INDEX_HREF, WALK_TOTAL, walkHref } from "../../lib/walk";
import { withBase } from "../../lib/site";

const STEP = 5;
const prev = chapterByStep(STEP - 1);
const next = chapterByStep(STEP + 1);

// The follow-the-money flow — OPC line items feed-sourced; the contribution,
// the actual award, and the abatement terms are cited constants.
const money = buildMoneyFlow();
// The per-job abatement value is the deciding number, and the record that pins it
// is non-public — so it's a labeled [open] screening band, not a record read.
const perJob = money.abatementPerJob;
const a = perJob.assumptions;
---

<Base
  title="What it costs the public — Chapter 4"
  section="site"
  description="The public's share of the data-center project arrives as roads, booked as a private gift. Read the cost estimate and the agreement that prices it."
>
  <div class="walk-chapter-page">
    <PathWayfinding step={STEP} />

    <div class="walk-chapter-eyebrow">Chapter {STEP} of {WALK_TOTAL} · the guided walk</div>
    <h1 class="walk-chapter-h1">What it costs the public</h1>

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        The public's share of this project arrives as roads — four roundabouts and
        two corridor rebuilds, dedicated to the county to maintain in perpetuity,
        and booked in the agreement that authorizes them as a <em>private</em>
        contribution from the developer. The estimate that sets the price is a Tetra
        Tech <strong>Opinion of Probable Cost</strong>. Read it the way an engineer
        would: start from the total, then ask what the total leaves out.
      </p>
    </div>

    <RecordTeardown record={OPC_TEARDOWN} layout="split" />

    <div class="td-beat">
      <div class="td-beat-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</div>
      <div class="td-beat-text">
        <b>and then —</b> that $14.2M estimate becomes a “private” contribution in
        the deal itself, where the clauses decide who really pays.
      </div>
    </div>

    <RecordTeardown record={RDA_TEARDOWN} layout="split" />

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        Read together, the two records say the same thing twice: a public-works
        number precise to the dollar sitting on a scope thin enough to hide a
        floodplain, wrapped in a contract whose quiet clauses decide who actually
        carries the cost.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="walk-interactive" aria-label="Follow the money">
      <h2 class="walk-explore-h">Follow the money</h2>
      <div class="mf-surface">
        <MoneyFlow client:only="react" data={money} />
        <noscript>
          <div class="dil-noscript">
            The interactive flow needs JavaScript — the table below is the same data.
          </div>
        </noscript>
      </div>

      <table class="dtable mf-table">
        <caption>
          The roadwork money, traced. The OPC line items are the records feed's own (no fork); the
          §5.5 refund consequence is <code>[inference]</code> — it turns on grant awards not in the document.
        </caption>
        <thead>
          <tr><th scope="col">Stage</th><th scope="col">Amount</th><th scope="col">Source</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Collected · “Company Contribution”</td>
            <td><strong>{fmtUsdFull(money.collectedUsd)}</strong></td>
            <td class="mf-td-cite">{money.collectedCite}</td>
          </tr>
          {
            money.opcItems.map((it) => (
              <tr class="mf-tr-item">
                <td>— {it.name}</td>
                <td>{fmtUsdFull(it.usd)}</td>
                <td class="mf-td-cite">OPC line item (records feed)</td>
              </tr>
            ))
          }
          <tr>
            <td>Tetra Tech OPC estimate · total</td>
            <td><strong>{fmtUsdFull(money.opcTotalUsd)}</strong></td>
            <td class="mf-td-cite">aedg/roundabouts.summary.opc.yaml (records feed)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>First actual award · Eagle Bridge (N. Cole)</td>
            <td><strong>~{fmtUsdFull(money.firstAward.usd)}</strong></td>
            <td class="mf-td-cite">{money.firstAward.cite}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>§5.5 grant-refund <code>[inference]</code></td>
            <td>surplus → developer</td>
            <td class="mf-td-cite">{money.refund.cite}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="callout callout--open mf-abate">
        <p class="callout-title">The parallel strand — the abatement</p>
        <p>
          A <strong>{money.abatement.pct}%</strong> real-property abatement for
          <strong> {money.abatement.years} years</strong> on a ~{fmtUsd(money.abatement.buildUsd)} build,
          pulled from the <strong>{money.abatement.taxBase}</strong> tax base — and the land was CAUV
          farmland, so converting it triggers tax recoupment. The public return: ~{money.abatement.jobs} jobs
          / ~{fmtUsd(money.abatement.payrollUsd)} payroll by 2030, from a near-zero today.
        </p>
        <p>
          What the abatement costs <em>per job</em> is the deciding number, and the record that would
          pin it — the School District Compensation Agreement — is <strong>non-public</strong>. So we
          don't leave the blank, and we don't invent a figure: we <em>model</em> it, and carry the
          answer as <span class="mf-tag mf-tag--open">[open]</span> until the record arrives. Across a
          few facility profiles the value lands between
          <strong>{fmtUsdM(perJob.lowUsd)}</strong> and <strong>{fmtUsdM(perJob.highUsd)}</strong> per job —
          about <strong>{fmtUsdM(perJob.centralUsd)}</strong> if you take the application's own ~{money.abatement.jobs} jobs
          at face value. Every one of those dwarfs the ~{fmtUsd(money.abatement.payrollUsd / money.abatement.jobs)} a
          job pays in a year.
        </p>

        <table class="dtable mf-perjob">
          <caption>
            The abated <em>base</em> (how much of the ~{fmtUsd(a.capexUsd)} is taxable building, not exempt
            equipment) and the <em>job count</em> are the two unknowns; each profile is a credible reading of
            them. The <strong>defense-hardened</strong> row is a modeling <em>what-if</em>, not a finding —
            the defense question itself stays <code>[open]</code> (#233).
          </caption>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Profile</th>
              <th scope="col">Building share</th>
              <th scope="col">Jobs</th>
              <th scope="col">Per job</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {
              perJob.profiles.map((p) => (
                <tr class={p.key === "stated" ? "mf-perjob-central" : undefined}>
                  <td>
                    {p.label}
                    <span class="mf-perjob-note">{p.note}</span>
                  </td>
                  <td>{Math.round(p.buildingShare * 100)}%</td>
                  <td>{p.jobs}</td>
                  <td><strong>{fmtUsdM(p.perJobUsd)}</strong></td>
                </tr>
              ))
            }
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="mf-perjob-model">
          <strong>How it's modeled.</strong> {money.abatement.pct}% × {money.abatement.years}-yr abatement
          <code>[verified]</code> (Res #548-25) on the building share of the ~{fmtUsd(a.capexUsd)} build
          <code>[verified]</code> (CRA §2, a non-binding estimate), taxed at Ohio's {Math.round(a.assessmentRatio * 100)}%
          assessment <code>[verified]</code> × ~{Math.round(a.effectiveMills * 1000)} effective mills
          <code>[assumption]</code> (the exact Elida rate isn't in the corpus). The result is a screening band,
          <code>[open]</code> — the real number is owed to the non-public School District Compensation Agreement.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="callout walk-takeaway">
      <p class="callout-title">What you can read anywhere now</p>
      <p>
        An <strong>Opinion of Probable Cost</strong> — check for the design-storm
        basis and whether detention is shown; their absence on a drainage line is a
        scope gap, not a rounding error. And a <strong>development agreement</strong>
        — the clauses on grant-refunds, records-notice, and competitive procurement
        are where the public's leverage is kept or quietly given away.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="walk-explore-h">Explore this in the library</h2>
    <div class="doors">
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/site/records/")}>
        <span class="door-label">The OPC record</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The full extraction — every roundabout's line items and subtotals.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/site/legal/")}>
        <span class="door-label">Legal history</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The Roadwork Development Agreement and the resolutions that adopted it.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/docs/economics")}>
        <span class="door-label">The economics</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The abatement and public-cost picture the roadwork sits inside.</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <nav class="walk-nav" aria-label="Chapter navigation">
      {
        prev?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev" href={walkHref(prev.slug)}>← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</a>
        ) : prev ? (
          <span class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev is-disabled" title="Drafting">← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</span>
        ) : (
          <span></span>
        )
      }
      <a class="walk-nav-leave" href={WALK_INDEX_HREF}>All chapters</a>
      {
        next?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next" href={walkHref(next.slug)}>{next.step}. {next.title} →</a>
        ) : next ? (
          <span class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next is-disabled" title="Drafting">{next.step}. {next.title} →</span>
        ) : (
          <span></span>
        )
      }
    </nav>
  </div>
</Base>
